BEGIN_TEXT
Use the elimination method to find all solutions of the system
\[
\begin{array}{l}
        3x^2-y^2 = 11, \\
        x^2+4y^2 = 8. \\
\end{array}
\]
The four solutions of the system are: \( (-a,-b), (-a,b),(a,-b)\), and \((a,b)\) with
positive numbers 
$BR
\(a=\) \{ans_rule(10) \} and \(b=\) \{ans_rule(10) \}.
$BR
END_TEXT

$ans1 = 2;
$ans2 = 1;

